===Etymology===
From {{etyl|ja|en}} {{term|琵琶|tr=びわ, biwa|lang=ja}}.

===Noun===
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|musical instrument|lang=en}} A plucked [[lute]], originating in the [[classical]] and [[traditional]] music of Japan, characterized by a pear-shaped body and four or five high frets, giving the instrument a distinctively [[twang]]y tone.

